99631.name: below 1.90$ a day
99631.description: The number of people living under 1.9$ a day using 2011 PPP.
99631.datasetName: Distribution of population between different poverty thresholds (World Bank, PovcalNet (2021))

source.name: World Bank, PovcalNet (2021)
source.dataPublishedBy: Our World in Data based on 'PovcalNet: the online tool for poverty measurement developed by the Development Research Group of the World Bank'
source.dataPublisherSource: World Bank, PovcalNet. Data are based on primary household survey data obtained from government statistical agencies and World Bank country departments.
source.additionalInfo:
Estimates of the number of people living below different poverty lines have been obtained using the Povcal online tool (version released 16th March 2021).

To calculate the number of people between two poverty lines we subtracted estimates of the number of people under the lower line from the number under the higher line. To calculate the number of people above a poverty line we subtracted the estimated number below that line from the total population (as reported within the Povcal database).
